('34045e5b-6633-8109-9fac-f4732dac2977', 'Retail Refill Implementation — Waitrose', 'Stalled', 'CH Sale', NULL, 'Needs Review', 'P2 — This Quarter', 'Medium — 30–70%', NULL, NULL, 'Retail Refill Implementation offer cue — Waitrose identified as priority premium retailer with clear sustainability-forward customer base.', NULL, NULL, 'Research Waitrose sustainability and own-brand procurement team. Identify sustainability buyer. Prepare Retail Refill One-pager with premium framing.', 'Sprint 24 Qualification Audit (2026-04-12): Score 53/100 — Needs Review. Trigger real (Retail Refill programme). Missing: Buyer Probable (no named contact at Waitrose). Access path weak. Decision Item open. To qualify: identify contact via advisor network, re-score ≥70.', 'Waitrose is a premium UK grocer with strong sustainability credentials and an affluent, values-led customer base. Their customers actively seek refill and zero-waste options. Waitrose has already run own-label packaging reduction initiatives and partners with sustainability-first brands. CH''s refill implementation model fits their premium service framing.', NULL, NULL, 'None', 53, 'Retail Refill Implementation offer cue — Waitrose identified as priority premium retailer with clear sustainability-forward customer base.', 'https://www.notion.so/Retail-Refill-Implementation-Waitrose-34045e5b663381099facf4732dac2977', '2026-04-12T19:51:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T19:51:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:02:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8115-a509-d1482028a889', 'iRefill × IDB — Investor Match', 'Stalled', 'Investor Match', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'IDB Notes reference Neil Khor exploring IDB support for Zero Waste cities/countries programming. iRefill LATAM deployment (Auto Mercado, Costa Rica) is a strong entry point. Coordinate with Neil Khor to activate IDB introduction in Q2 2026.', 'Match proposed by deal-flow-agent (investor-matchmaker) — Score: 60/90. Funder: IDB — Inter-American Development Bank (34045e5b-6633-81c4-b636-e94960bd5bf8). Signals fired: (1) Sector overlap — IDB themes Public Sector/Climate/Cities/Zero Waste/Policy match iRefill Reuse/Refill/Retail/LATAM operations (+25); (2) Stage signal — IDB Notes explicitly name iRefill as LATAM-aligned portfolio startup (+15); (3) Existing relationship — IDB Notes reference iRefill directly; ZWF Forum/COP31 shared context via CH (+12); (4) Startup type — circular/refill/sustainability in both records (+8). Run date: 2026-04-12. Confidence: Medium. This is a SPECIFIC funder record separate from the generic ''iRefill — Investor Match'' placeholder.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/iRefill-IDB-Investor-Match-34045e5b66338115a509d1482028a889', '2026-04-12T13:13:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T13:13:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:04:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-811a-8d04-d7fd9579d6eb', 'EIC Accelerator (Horizon Europe) — iRefill', 'Stalled', 'Grant', NULL, 'Not Scored', 'P2 — This Quarter', 'Medium — 30–70%', '34045e5b-6633-81fe-b99b-e6ea6a6f500e', 'Horizon Europe / EIC Accelerator', 'UK Horizon Association membership active since 2024. EIC cut-offs approx 3x/year.', NULL, NULL, 'Review current EIC Accelerator cut-off dates (eic.ec.europa.eu). Prepare Step 1 application: business case + innovation description + market sizing. Likely next cut-off Q3 2026.', NULL, 'iRefill''s circular economy solution fits EIC Green Deal cluster. UK companies eligible since Horizon Association 2024. Pilot evidence (34% plastic reduction, borough partnership) provides the real-world validation EIC looks for. Up to €17.5M combined grant + equity.', NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, 'UK Horizon Association membership active since 2024. EIC cut-offs approx 3x/year.', 'https://www.notion.so/EIC-Accelerator-Horizon-Europe-iRefill-34045e5b6633811a8d04d7fd9579d6eb', '2026-04-12T18:20:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:20:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:04:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-813a-a7d3-d2460b365d03', 'Beeok × World Bank — Investor Match', 'Stalled', 'Investor Match', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'World Bank entry point is ZWF Forum 2026 Istanbul event (per WB Notes). Position Beeok as the MRV/ESG measurement infrastructure partner for World Bank Zero Waste programming. Neil Khor is the bridge — coordinate before Istanbul. Active SAFE round in parallel.', 'Match proposed by deal-flow-agent (investor-matchmaker) — Score: 62/90. Funder: World Bank (34045e5b-6633-81d8-b156-d042ca68be9d). Signals fired: (1) Sector overlap — World Bank themes Public Sector/Climate/Cities/Zero Waste match Beeok Carbon MRV/ESG/Waste/Plastic Footprint (+27); (2) Stage signal — World Bank Notes reference ''Zero Waste cities/countries programming'' — Beeok''s MRV platform is directly relevant at scale (+15); (3) Existing relationship — Beeok Grant record in Opportunities DB explicitly names World Bank as active in MRV/ESG space; ZWF Forum/COP31 shared entry point (+10); (4) Startup type — sustainability/ESG/carbon/cities in both records (+10). Run date: 2026-04-12. Confidence: Medium. Separate from generic ''Beeok — Investor Match'' placeholder.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/Beeok-World-Bank-Investor-Match-34045e5b6633813aa7d3d2460b365d03', '2026-04-12T13:13:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T13:13:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:04:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8140-8bdd-f0436a12b188', 'Ellen MacArthur CE100 Network — Common House', 'Stalled', 'Partnership', NULL, 'Not Scored', 'P3 — Backlog', NULL, '34045e5b-6633-8147-8efa-d6c44920533e', 'Ellen MacArthur Foundation', 'Sprint 19 research agent confirmed: EMF is a network/convening org, not a grant funder. Reclassified from Grant to Partnership. Watch for EMF challenge prizes as secondary signal.', NULL, NULL, 'Contact EMF philanthropy team (philanthropy@emf.org) for CE100 network membership inquiry. Clarify whether CH or iRefill qualifies as CE100 member vs. partner. Track EMF challenge announcements for occasional prize opportunities. Do NOT treat as grant opportunity.', NULL, 'Ellen MacArthur Foundation does NOT offer external grants. CE100 is a membership/convening network for companies implementing circular economy. Common House and iRefill have strong circular economy mission alignment. CE100 membership would provide credibility, knowledge access, and co-funding signal value rather than direct funding. Research confirmed: EMF occasionally runs time-limited challenges with small prizes (~£30k) but no regular grant programme.', NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, 'Sprint 19 research agent confirmed: EMF is a network/convening org, not a grant funder. Reclassified from Grant to Partnership. Watch for EMF challenge prizes as secondary signal.', 'https://www.notion.so/Ellen-MacArthur-CE100-Network-Common-House-34045e5b663381408bddf0436a12b188', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:04:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8140-bf97-c6172db5c865', 'Esmée Fairbairn Foundation — Zero Waste Community Grant', 'Stalled', 'Grant', NULL, 'Not Scored', 'P3 — Backlog', NULL, '34045e5b-6633-81b1-9188-fb99d277daf8', 'Esmée Fairbairn Foundation', 'Esmée Fairbairn funder record created Sprint 19. Eligibility confirmation flagged as Decision Item (Bloque 8).', NULL, NULL, 'Confirm whether Common House or iRefill has nonprofit/CIC entity that meets Esmée Fairbairn eligibility. Review current programme areas. Check application windows (typically spring/autumn).', NULL, 'Esmée Fairbairn funds UK civil society and social change organisations in environment and society. CH''s zero waste portfolio (iRefill) and community activation angle is well-matched. Grant requires a nonprofit or social enterprise lead — eligibility of CH entity type needs confirmation before proceeding.', NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, 'Esmée Fairbairn funder record created Sprint 19. Eligibility confirmation flagged as Decision Item (Bloque 8).', 'https://www.notion.so/Esm-e-Fairbairn-Foundation-Zero-Waste-Community-Grant-34045e5b66338140bf97c6172db5c865', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:02:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8143-a940-fab818139102', 'Beeok — CH Sale', 'Stalled', 'CH Sale', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Identify 2–3 multilateral or NGO clients with ESG/carbon reporting mandates that Beeok''s platform could serve. ZWF Forum network is a starting point.', 'Beeok = carbon MRV + ESG SaaS. 150+ clients, break-even. CH angle: introduce to multilateral / NGO contacts. 15% rev share to CH. Opportunity created 2026-04-12.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/Beeok-CH-Sale-34045e5b66338143a940fab818139102', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:05:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8148-bba3-d172fcd21a64', 'Retail Refill Implementation — Morrisons', 'Stalled', 'CH Sale', NULL, 'Below Threshold', 'P3 — Backlog', 'Low — <30%', NULL, NULL, 'Retail Refill Implementation offer cue — Morrisons flagged as P3 target with vertical integration advantage.', NULL, NULL, 'Research Morrisons sustainability and store format innovation contacts. Assess whether CD&R ownership changes procurement dynamics.', 'Sprint 24 Qualification Audit (2026-04-12): Score 38/100 — Below Threshold. Weakest of five retailers. Lowest sustainability market positioning. No named contact, no access path, no buyer trigger. Decision Item open recommending Closed Lost / Not a fit.', 'Morrisons has vertical integration (own manufacturing and farming supply chain) which makes refill infrastructure uniquely compelling — they control more of the supply chain than competitors and can pilot proprietary product formats. Their sustainability programme is less advanced than Co-op or Waitrose, creating room for CH to position as the delivery partner.', NULL, NULL, 'None', 38, 'Retail Refill Implementation offer cue — Morrisons flagged as P3 target with vertical integration advantage.', 'https://www.notion.so/Retail-Refill-Implementation-Morrisons-34045e5b66338148bba3d172fcd21a64', '2026-04-12T19:51:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T19:51:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:02:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8156-81d5-c0b313f5166a', 'EIC Accelerator (Horizon Europe) — Yenxa', 'Stalled', 'Grant', NULL, 'Not Scored', 'P3 — Backlog', NULL, '34045e5b-6633-81fe-b99b-e6ea6a6f500e', 'Horizon Europe / EIC Accelerator', 'Horizon Europe funder created Sprint 19. iRefill is already tracked against EIC (Opportunity #3). Need to assess which startup is better positioned for EIC first.', NULL, NULL, 'Confirm Yenxa R&D investment track record and TRL level. Assess if Yenxa team has written any EU grant applications previously. Check EIC Accelerator cut-off dates for 2026.', NULL, 'EIC Accelerator targets deep tech and innovation-driven SMEs across EU/UK. Yenxa''s technology-forward model in its domain positions it as a plausible EIC Accelerator candidate — pending confirmation of technical depth and previous R&D investment. EIC Accelerator provides up to €2.5M grant + equity investment.', NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, 'Horizon Europe funder created Sprint 19. iRefill is already tracked against EIC (Opportunity #3). Need to assess which startup is better positioned for EIC first.', 'https://www.notion.so/EIC-Accelerator-Horizon-Europe-Yenxa-34045e5b6633815681d5c0b313f5166a', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:02:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-816d-aa7a-e3467626c962', 'Innovate UK Smart Grant — iRefill', 'New', 'Grant', NULL, 'Not Scored', 'P1 — Act Now', 'Medium — 30–70%', '34045e5b-6633-810a-a0c5-d98e3fc12337', 'Innovate UK', 'Innovate UK Smart grants open approx 3x/year. Next window likely Q2/Q3 2026. No open call confirmed as of April 2026.', NULL, NULL, 'Check current Smart grant competition on ukri.org. Register on Innovation Funding Service (IFS). Prepare 3-page project outline.', NULL, 'iRefill is UK-registered climate tech company with proven borough pilot (34% plastic reduction in 90 days). Qualifies under Clean Growth and Net Zero themes. Pilot evidence is exactly what Innovate UK looks for in Smart grant applications.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Innovate UK Smart grants open approx 3x/year. Next window likely Q2/Q3 2026. No open call confirmed as of April 2026.', 'https://www.notion.so/Innovate-UK-Smart-Grant-iRefill-34045e5b6633816daa7ae3467626c962', '2026-04-12T18:19:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:19:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:19:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8176-a75c-d0763baf5130', 'Beeok — Investor Match', 'Stalled', 'Investor Match', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Beeok has active fundraise (15% SAFE discount confirmed). Identify CH network contacts who can accelerate the round. Introduce to at least one investor in April.', 'ARR ~$1M USD, break-even, 150+ clients. Active SAFE round. 15% SAFE discount to CH portfolio contacts. CH holds 15% rev share + 7.5% equity. Opportunity created 2026-04-12.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/Beeok-Investor-Match-34045e5b66338176a75cd0763baf5130', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:04:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-817d-9120-d8bdc63d8f0a', 'Retail Refill Implementation — Co-op', 'Stalled', 'CH Sale', NULL, 'Needs Review', 'P2 — This Quarter', 'Medium — 30–70%', NULL, NULL, 'Retail Refill Implementation offer cue — Co-op identified as priority sustainability-forward UK retailer. EPR compliance 2025–2026 creating urgency across UK grocery.', NULL, NULL, 'Identify sustainability procurement contact at Co-op. Request exploratory call. Bring Auto Mercado case evidence and iRefill borough pilot data.', 'Sprint 24 Qualification Audit (2026-04-12): Score 59/100 — Needs Review. Trigger real (Retail Refill programme). Missing: Buyer Probable (no named contact at Co-op sustainability/format team). Decision Item open. To qualify: add named contact, re-score ≥70.', 'Co-op is the UK''s most sustainability-forward major grocer. They have publicly committed to reducing plastic packaging and have piloted refill stations in select stores. Auto Mercado precedent (Central America) and iRefill UK borough pilots provide direct proof of delivery. CH can offer a structured programme from pilot to full store rollout — exactly the scale Co-op needs.', NULL, NULL, 'None', 59, 'Retail Refill Implementation offer cue — Co-op identified as priority sustainability-forward UK retailer. EPR compliance 2025–2026 creating urgency across UK grocery.', 'https://www.notion.so/Retail-Refill-Implementation-Co-op-34045e5b6633817d9120d8bdc63d8f0a', '2026-04-12T19:51:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T19:51:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:02:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-818b-b135-fe7242ff6cd7', 'LIFE Programme — Zero Waste Cities Consortium', 'New', 'Grant', NULL, 'Not Scored', 'P3 — Backlog', 'Low — <30%', '34045e5b-6633-814b-9829-e675cbd7720d', 'LIFE Programme (EU)', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Identify EU-based consortium partner (municipality, NGO, or company). Review LIFE 2026 work programme when published. UK partner needs EU lead organisation to qualify.', NULL, 'LIFE Zero Pollution subprogram aligns with refill infrastructure reducing single-use plastic. iRefill''s system is exactly the kind of circular economy infrastructure LIFE funds. CH coordinates multi-stakeholder consortium.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/LIFE-Programme-Zero-Waste-Cities-Consortium-34045e5b6633818bb135fe7242ff6cd7', '2026-04-12T18:20:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:20:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:20:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-8197-897e-e332d6fee9a9', 'UKRI Circular Economy Challenge — iRefill R&D', 'New', 'Grant', NULL, 'Not Scored', 'P3 — Backlog', NULL, '34045e5b-6633-812d-ac1e-f19ea8726b70', 'UKRI (UK Research and Innovation)', 'UKRI funder record created Sprint 19. iRefill borough partnership results seeded in Content Pipeline as Signal item.', NULL, NULL, 'Identify current UKRI Circular Economy challenge round. Check iRefill''s R&D spend qualifies as eligible activity. Draft 2-page concept note for initial UKRI contact.', NULL, 'iRefill''s refill infrastructure is a direct application of circular economy R&D — waste reduction, packaging elimination, behaviour change at scale. UKRI Circular Economy challenge specifically funds SMEs developing reuse/refill solutions. iRefill''s borough partnership data provides evidence base for scaling claims.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'UKRI funder record created Sprint 19. iRefill borough partnership results seeded in Content Pipeline as Signal item.', 'https://www.notion.so/UKRI-Circular-Economy-Challenge-iRefill-R-D-34045e5b66338197897ee332d6fee9a9', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T18:24:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-819a-84f8-ef924d270b53', 'iRefill — CH Sale', 'Stalled', 'CH Sale', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Identify next CH-originated client opportunity that iRefill hardware could serve. Auto Mercado pilot (May 2026) is the proof of concept — use results to pitch next retailer or distributor in LATAM.', 'This CH Sale tracks commercial revenue from iRefill deployments originated by CH. 15% revenue share applies. Different from the CH + Startup Shared Auto Mercado opportunity. Next sales target: identify post-Auto Mercado retailer by Q3 2026. Opportunity created 2026-04-12.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/iRefill-CH-Sale-34045e5b6633819a84f8ef924d270b53', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:05:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-81a0-949e-fc27219b8847', 'SUFI — CH Sale', 'Stalled', 'CH Sale', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Define first commercial target: which clients would buy from SUFI through CH after market entry? Draft a target client profile by Q2 2026.', 'CH holds 25% Venture Builder equity. Market entry mid-2026. Opportunity tracks future CH-facilitated sales. Opportunity created 2026-04-12.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/SUFI-CH-Sale-34045e5b663381a0949efc27219b8847', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:05:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-81a6-805c-e5feaa077b03', 'SUFI — Investor Match', 'Stalled', 'Investor Match', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Identify 2–3 impact investors active in LATAM / circular economy / refillable consumer goods stage. SUFI market entry is mid-2026 — funding window is now.', 'CH co-creation (25% Venture Builder equity). Pre-revenue. Prototype expected Q1 2026, market entry mid-2026. LATAM focus. Opportunity created 2026-04-12.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/SUFI-Investor-Match-34045e5b663381a6805ce5feaa077b03', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T12:59:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:05:00.000Z'),
('34045e5b-6633-81b0-b54e-e5a7fecd784b', 'Beeok × IDB — Investor Match', 'Stalled', 'Investor Match', NULL, 'Not Scored', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Beeok''s MRV/ESG platform is directly relevant to IDB''s Zero Waste cities programming. Active SAFE round (15% discount) is open. Coordinate with Neil Khor to fast-track IDB introduction — Beeok has $1M ARR and 150+ clients, strongest commercial profile in the portfolio for this funder.', 'Match proposed by deal-flow-agent (investor-matchmaker) — Score: 62/90. Funder: IDB — Inter-American Development Bank (34045e5b-6633-81c4-b636-e94960bd5bf8). Signals fired: (1) Sector overlap — IDB themes Climate/Cities/Zero Waste/Policy strongly match Beeok Carbon MRV/ESG/Waste/Multilaterals (+27); (2) Stage signal — IDB Notes name Beeok explicitly among LATAM-active portfolio startups (+15); (3) Existing relationship — IDB Notes directly reference Beeok as LATAM-aligned; ZWF Forum shared context (+10); (4) Startup type — sustainability/ESG/carbon/cities present in both records (+10). Run date: 2026-04-12. Confidence: Medium. P1 escalation — score ≥ 70 threshold not reached but strong structural fit. Separate from generic ''Beeok — Investor Match'' placeholder.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'None', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.notion.so/Beeok-IDB-Investor-Match-34045e5b663381b0b54ee5a7fecd784b', '2026-04-12T13:13:00.000Z', '2026-04-12T13:13:00.000Z', '2026-04-15T14:04:00.000Z')
